Jesse Ewart (born 31 July 1994) is an Australian-born Irish cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Continental team Terengganu Cycling Team.
In September 2024, Jesse was given a three year ban by the Union Cycliste Internationale. He tested positive for EPO.
